  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with locally advanced suqamous cell carcinoma of the head and neck region receive a
      hypoxia scan either by magnetic resonance tomography, computed tomography or
      fluoromisonidazole (FMISO)-PET-CT. Patients presenting with hypoxia are randomized into
      standard therapy consisting of intensity modulated radiotherapy (IMRT) with 70 Gy plus either
      5-fluorouracil/mitomycin C or cisplatinum (Arm A) or a dose escalation of 10% (77Gy) to the
      hypoxic volume applied via simultaneous integrated boost in addition to the standard
      treatment (Arm B).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
